PROJECT:-Mini-Linter

A JavaScript project from the Parsity Dev30 bootcamp that analyzes and manipulates a text story using array methods and object manipulation.

Features
Word Count: Counts total words in the story

Overused Word Detection: Tracks how many times specific overused words appear

Sentence Counter: Counts sentences based on punctuation

Word Filtering: Removes unnecessary words from the story

Smart Filtering: Removes overused words every other time they appear (keeps 1st, 3rd, 5th occurrences)

Frequency Analyzer: Finds the most frequently appearing word in the entire story

Word Replacement: Replaces overused words with alternatives

Technologies Used
Vanilla JavaScript

Array methods: .split(), .filter(), .reduce(), .forEach(), .map()

Object manipulation for word counting